[~spark] I assumed the credentials for role 'loadbalancer-vm-000840838253-testing-gui-2174' and tried to upload 'AccessLogs-GUI-2174/testobj_s3curl_lb' to 'testing-gui-2174' and I'm still observing the issue of failing IAM checks

{noformat}
2015-10-16 16:30:28 DEBUG 000047498 PolicyEngineImpl         | Request is rejected by authorization check, due to decision DEFAULT
2015-10-16 16:30:28 DEBUG 000047498 Permissions              | Denied resource access to s3:object:testing-gui-2174/AccessLogs-GUI-2174/testobj_s3curl_lb for com.eucalyptus.auth.euare.UserPrincipalImpl@339a71a4: Access to the resource is denied
{noformat}

Executing other actions permitted by the following policy also failed with the same IAM check failures 
{noformat}
# euare-rolegetpolicy loadbalancer-vm-000840838253-testing-gui-2174 -p euca-internal-loadbalancer-vm-policy-accesslog --as-account '(eucalyptus)loadbalancing'
{"Statement":[ {"Effect":"Allow","Action":["s3:ListBucket"],"Resource":"arn:aws:s3:::testing-gui-2174" },{"Action": ["s3:GetObject", "s3:PutObject", "s3:GetObjectAcl", "s3:PutObjectAcl"],"Effect": "Allow","Resource": ["arn:aws:s3:::testing-gui-2174/AccessLogs-GUI-2174/*"]}]}
{noformat}

[~swathi] Would you try using a different (or none) bucket prefix. Perhaps that is where the failure happens. You can do it using:
{noformat}
 eulb-modify-lb-attributes testing-gui-2174 AccessLog.Enabled=True AccessLog.EmitInterval=5 AccessLog.S3BucketName=testing-gui-2174 AccessLog.S3BucketPrefix=prefix
{noformat}
